    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6830" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀνομάζω</span></b> , ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀνόμαζον</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὠνόμασα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">call</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">address by
            name</span> (<i><span class="en">Il. 22.415</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.68</span></i>), <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">name, mention;</span>
          the phrase <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔπος τ᾽ ἔφατ̓ ἔκ</span> (adv.)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τ᾽ ὀνόμαζεν</span> (and ‘familiarly
          addressed’ him) is always followed either by the name of the person
          addressed or by some substantial equivalent for the name.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
